        <div id="right_content">
        	<div id="aboutus" class="text_7" style="border-bottom:6px solid #bdbdbd;">
            	<p class="text_6" style="padding-bottom:20px;">About Tingog 2015</p>
                <p style="padding-bottom:20px;">Tingog 2015 is both a technological tool and a strategy. Technology, mainly in the form of SMS and the Internet, it is used as a platform for ordinary people to directly provide feedback to government agencies and expect timely, reasonable results. As a strategy, Tingog 2015 involves bringing together communities, civil society groups, local government and the media to ensure that the most pressing issues are identified and immediately and properly addressed.</p>
                <p style="padding-bottom:20px;">With only four years left to achieve the MDGs, accountability, transparency and citizen empowerment are crucial given the country's national development. Tingog 2015 paves the way for citizens to become partners in development by giving them a "voice" in local development planning.</p>
                <p style="padding-bottom:20px;">The Provincial Government of Agusan Del Sur, the City Government of Tabaco, and the Provincial Government of Albay are committed to enabling citizens to report on services and to addressing the issues raised. Tingog 2015 is being facilitated by Social Watch Philippines in collaboration with United Nations Millennium Campaign and other partners and stakeholders. During its initial stages, the initiative will focus on health services in Tabaco, Albay before covering other MDG-related services.</p>
                <p>For the first time in Philippine history, the three major telecommunications Globe Telecom, SMART Communications, and Sun Cellular are working together to allow citizens to send in their reports using a four-digit number code, 2015 - the deadline of MDG achievement.</p>
